173
00:15:23,299 --> 00:15:24,592
Sunday night, you'll call him back,

174
00:15:24,675 --> 00:15:26,760
and by Monday,
he'll be kissin' the ground you walk on.

175
00:15:26,844 --> 00:15:28,429
Exactly.

176
00:15:28,512 --> 00:15:30,806
In the meantime,
you said we was gonna have some fun,

177
00:15:30,889 --> 00:15:32,600
so let's have some!

178
00:15:33,350 --> 00:15:35,060
- All right.
- Okay.

179
00:15:45,237 --> 00:15:46,947
All right.

180
00:15:51,744 --> 00:15:52,828
Okay.

181
00:15:52,911 --> 00:15:54,955
- Let's dance.
- All right.

182
00:16:00,794 --> 00:16:04,214
<i>I woke up in a hotel,
I didn't know what to do</i>

183
00:16:04,298 --> 00:16:07,134
<i>I turned the TV on,
and wrote a letter to you</i>

184
00:16:07,217 --> 00:16:10,346
<i>The news was talkin' 'bout a dragnet
up on the interstate...</i>

185
00:16:10,429 --> 00:16:13,140
Thelma. That's your name? Thelma?
That's a lovely name.

186
00:16:13,223 --> 00:16:15,309
I don't know what I'm doing.

187
00:16:15,392 --> 00:16:17,519
Follow me, Thelma.

188
00:16:19,438 --> 00:16:21,940
- Ma'am, you wanna dance a little?
- Sure.

189
00:16:22,024 --> 00:16:25,194
<i>Since I left California, baby,
things have gotten worse</i>

190
00:16:25,277 --> 00:16:28,739
<i>Seems the land of opportunity,
for me is just a curse</i>

191
00:16:28,822 --> 00:16:31,950
<i>Tell that judge in Bakersfield
my trial'll have to wait</i>

192
00:16:33,786 --> 00:16:37,081
